				<p class="paragraph--2">To introduce a broad IT risk management effort, as well as initiate a centralized vulnerability management initiative, the bank created a chief information security officer position to oversee the program. The security program, in addition to putting the proper people and processes in place, also included the right technological defenses: anti-malware, security policy management, measures to protect the network, log management, database activity monitoring and event correlation. <b><i>“I also can’t stress enough how important the support and guidance provided by our top management was to these efforts,”</i></b> says Grigorescu. <b><i>“I have friends and partners working inside other financial institutions in similar positions who are grasping for just a little attention and a few figures in their budgets,”</i></b> he says.</p>
